{{DISPLAYTITLE:Level 100.2: "Desolate Beach"}}{{Blurbackground|file=Level 100.2.png|opacity=75%}}{{Audio|file=Lifting You.mp3|loop=yes|align=center|secrettext=Lifting You}}{{Class 0|hexagon=κ|color-h=230|class=Kappa|color-s=90%|safety=Safe|security=Stable|entity=Emotional Hazards}}'''Level 100.2''' is a sublevel between [[Level 100]] and [[Level 101]]. It has become a common transitory space for wanderers looking to reach [[Level 100]] due to its abundance of entrances and having a guaranteed exit to its [[Level 100|parent level]].

== Description ==
{{Blurimage|file=Level 102.1 2.png|caption=The first ever recorded image of '''Level 100.2'''.}}'''Level 100.2''', commonly referred to as the "Desolate Beach," resembles an infinitely stretching beach with a derelict appearance.

The beach sand is a bright shade of faded yellow and described as grainy to the touch. Some of the sand may contain metal cans, glass shards, and metal objects buried within it; therefore, it is important to wear shoes to avoid injury. Occasionally, patches of grass and palm trees grow on the sand of '''Level 100.2'''.

Various objects, such as wooden chairs and parasols, can be found scattered throughout the beach. Most of these objects appear deteriorated and slightly embedded in the ground, though a few are recorded as being in pristine condition. Near these chairs and parasols, one can find bottles of [[Object 1|Almond Water]]<ref>If the chair and parasol next to the bottle appear derelict, it means the Almond Water has expired.</ref> and sunscreen, though the latter is not necessary for exploration, as the sun appears to have a much weaker influence at this level. Other rarer objects, mainly rusty refrigerated carts filled with popsicles and ice cream, can be found in more distant areas of '''Level 100.2'''. While most of the food in these carts is safe for consumption, it may cause mild stomachaches along with a low fever.

The sea is composed of clear water with minimal residue, and its tides are relatively calm<ref>While the tides do become very agitated once one swims far enough from the coast, these tides never reach the coast.</ref>. The water's temperature stays at a lukewarm 28°C. The farther one swims out into the sea, the cloudier the sky will become, and the sea will get more agitated. On certain occasions, typically during sunrise and dawn, various boats of different sizes can spawn near the shore, though there is little to no incentive to explore them due to their lack of resources. The boats disappear around 2 hours after they spawn.{{Blurimage|file=Alloi Allim.png|caption=A photograph of '''Level 100.2''', notice the large number of boats near shore.}}Occasionally, one can find small huts made of wood and straw. While most are empty, some contain valuable resources such as [[Object 6|Moth Jelly]] and bottles of [[Object 12|Liquid Pain]].

The data above may have minor discrepancies because the level subtly adjusts to match the wanderer's memories. These differences include the presence of popular local brands on objects, slight terrain variations based on previously visited beaches, and the amount of trash in the seawater and sand. If the wanderer has never seen a beach, the level will appear in its simplest form.

The most prevalent anomaly in '''Level 100.2''' is its distinct lack of saturation, with 50% less pigment than its [[Level 100|parent level]]. This phenomenon affects all of the level, including the wanderer and the objects they bring.

'''Level 100.2''' does not have a day-night cycle, as the sun immediately returns to a sunrise position just before setting. This cycle repeats every 12 hours and may bring instability to this level after each restart.

The temperature of the beach stays at a chill 16°C, dropping to 11°C at sunrise and sunset. Even with these temperatures, the seawater remains consistently warm.

This level is affected by [[Phenomenon 15]], which separates each wanderer into a separate copy of it.

Upon entering this level, the wanderer will gradually feel more melancholic and develop a strong longing for the past, especially for those who've associated beaches with good memories. This can be overcome by submerging in the water, which will gradually calm the wanderer.

Any consumable objects brought to this level will slowly lose their color and taste, eventually becoming monochrome, signifying the food has become tasteless.

=== The Restaurant ===
'''The Restaurant''' is a section of '''Level 100.2''' that can be accessed by locating a large restaurant structure 250 meters away from the sea and entering through the double glass doors.{{Blurimage|file=Level 100,2 restaurant.png|caption=A photo of '''The Restaurant''' section in '''Level 100.2'''.}}'''The Restaurant''', like the rest of the level, stretches infinitely from east to west, but is finite in width, being 100 meters wide, eventually stopping at a wall with large unbreakable windows featuring a coastal city.

'''The Restaurant'''<nowiki/>'s architectural style is characterized by frequent use along coastlines, with a polished marble ceiling, wooden floors and walls, and large windows. Unlike the rest of the level, all surfaces from '''The Restaurant''' are pristine and well-kept. This area is furnished with sets of tables covered in checkered cloth and chairs. The counter, dividing '''The Restaurant''' from a locked kitchen area, is lined with polished plates and shiny silverware.

'''The Restaurant''' is full of trays carrying diverse assortments of seafood and coconut water. If a tray happens to be empty, it will be restocked in a week by unknown means. The food can also be found sitting on plates around the restaurant.

The Restaurant does not adjust itself to fit a wanderer's memories, nor does it cause one to become melancholic, but most describe themselves as being confused upon entering this section.

== Entities ==
There are no entities in '''Level 100.2''' due to the presence of [[Phenomenon 15]].

== Entrances and Exits ==

=== Entrances ===

* Noclipping into a striped parasol in The Grass Halls of [[Level 99]] will lead here.
* One can occasionally find a restaurant at [[Level 9.85]]; walking into it will take one to the '''Restaurant''' section of '''Level 100.2'''.
* Some sections of [[Level 402]] will seamlessly transition into this level.
* There is a small chance that an exit in any level to [[Level 100]] will take one here instead.
* Noclipping into a large pile of sand in [[Level 11]] will lead here.
* Accidental noclipping on the beach of [[Level 330]] takes one to this level.
* Burying oneself in sand during a spire event in [[Level 100.6]] will lead one here.
*

=== Exits ===
* Submerging entirely in water for a minute will cause one to resurface on [[Level 100]].
* Entering certain boats may cause the interior to transition to [[Level 17]].
* Swimming far enough from the coast will cause the environment to transition into [[Level 7]].
* Consuming certain foods from the restaurant may lead to [[Level 167]].
* Succumbing to suicidal ideation in '''Level 100.2''' correlated to its effects will lead one to [[Level 888]].
* [[Level 7.1|Something touches you in the water.]]
